commit.message: Upgrade pip on appveyor before installing tox [skip travis]
Updated license link in the svg2pdf script
Release svglib 0.9.1

Update utils.py to handle mishandled circular arcs

There are some cases where svglib will incorrectly render circular arcs.
This appears to stem from the `r > 1` case of `end_point_to_center_parameters`
when r is close to 1, resulting in the r value being kept at 1 (rather
than 1 / r -1 , which should be approximately 0).

Initial patch by Andrew Backer <awbacker@gmail.com>
